tp:treatment-sec.p:
This species is similar to 

Rh. micholitzi
(Belokobylskij, 2001)

comb. nov.
from 
Papua New Guinea
(
Belokobylskij 2001b
), but differs from latter in having the vertex entirely transversely striate (mainly granulate and only laterally with short striation in 

Rh. micholitzi

), frons entirely coarsely reticulaterugose (mainly granulate in 

Rh. micholitzi

), precoxal sulcus coarsely crenulate (smooth in 

Rh. micholitzi

), pterostigma pale in basal third (entirely dark brown in 

Rh. micholitzi

), mediocubital vein (M+CU1) of fore wing distinctly curved in apical half (weakly curved in 

Rh. micholitzi

), nervulus (cu-a) distinctly postfurcal (almost interstitial in 

Rh. micholitzi

), hind tarsus distinctly longer than hind tibia (almost equal to it in 

Rh. micholitzi

), and the first metasomal tergite short (long in 

Rh. micholitzi

).
